# Delete Account — Echo Words

**Last updated: May 28, 2026**

---

## Request Account Deletion

You can delete your Echo Words account and all associated data at any time. We offer two methods:

---

### Method 1: In-App (Recommended)

The fastest way to delete your account:

1. Open **Echo Words** app
2. Tap the **Settings** icon (top-right)
3. Scroll to the bottom
4. Tap **Delete Account & Data**
5. Confirm the action

Your account and all data will be deleted immediately.

---

### Method 2: By Email

If you cannot access the app, send a deletion request by email:

**Email:** teovox4@gmail.com

**Subject:** Delete Echo Words Account

**Include in the message:**
- Your anonymous user ID (if known — visible in Settings → About)
- Confirmation that you want all data permanently deleted

We will process your request within **30 days** and send a confirmation email when complete.

---

## What Gets Deleted

When you delete your account, we permanently remove:

- ✅ Anonymous user account (Firebase Authentication)
- ✅ All cloud-synced game progress (scores, badges, streaks)
- ✅ Daily Mystery progress and history
- ✅ Coin balance and ad watch history
- ✅ All settings and preferences

---

## What May Be Retained

For legitimate reasons, we may retain:

- **Aggregated, anonymized analytics** (no personal identifiers, used for app improvement)
- **Crash logs** (for up to 90 days, used for debugging)

These retained items cannot be used to identify you personally.

---

## Important Notes

- Account deletion is **permanent and irreversible**
- Once deleted, your data cannot be recovered
- You can create a new account by reinstalling the app — but previous progress will be lost
- Local game data on your device will also be cleared

